{"id":"minime-q2r","content_hash":"0e7024e393b545dac29e7d91ad82098ce0c623b2e457bbc61c7c13650c013dd3","title":"Implement hybrid search (semantic + keyword) for RAG queries","description":"Semantic search alone can miss exact keyword matches (e.g., 'Naples' search didn't find all Naples references). Implemented hybrid search that combines: 1) Semantic vector search (cosine similarity) 2) Keyword text search (ILIKE) with automatic keyword extraction from queries. Results prioritize exact keyword matches while still using semantic relevance. Increased result limit from 5 to 50. Added debugging info (keyword_matches, semantic_matches, avg_similarity) to response.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-11-13T08:47:31.315162397-07:00","updated_at":"2025-11-13T08:47:39.649549246-07:00","source_repo":"."}
